#importing libray required for convertion to datetime
import datetime as dt
import calendar
comcast_df ['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(comcast_df ['Date'])
comcast_df ['Month'] =comcast_df ['Date'].dt.month
comcast_df ['Month'] =comcast_df ['Month'].apply(lambda x:calendar.month_abbr[x])
comcast_df .drop('Date_month_year',axis =1, inplace = True)

number of complaints at monthly and daily granularity levels¶














Daily¶












In [24]:



    


import seaborn as sns
plt.figure(figsize=(25,5))
sns.barplot(x=comcast_df['Date'].dt.date.unique(), y=comcast_df['Date'].value_counts())
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.ylabel('ticket counts')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.title(' Date VS count of tickets ')
plt.show()



    















    




























Monthly¶












In [25]:



    


plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))
sns.barplot(x=comcast_df['Month'].unique(), y=comcast_df['Month']. value_counts())
plt.ylabel('ticket counts')
plt.xlabel('Monthly')
plt.title(' Month VS count of tickets ')
plt.show()



    















    




























state wise status of complaints in a stacked bar chart¶

Comcast_Stacked = Stacked.unstack(level=1)
